[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering the rules regarding reflection in tests, and it seems I shouldn't use it directly unless the public API naturally requires it. For instance, the Executable constructor is necessary for passing to the public API method. The BeanRegistrationCodeFragments API requires Executable, so using Class.getConstructor in this context might be tracked. Since direct reflection is discouraged, I'll look into using RegisteredBean.resolveConstructorOrFactoryMethod instead to get the constructor, which aligns more with the public API.
